Summary: The course, titled "Vision Systems," will take place from January 6 to January 10, 2025. The instructor, Tian Jing, will cover topics such as computer vision systems, foundations of computer vision systems, and vision systems using machine learning. There will be workshops on each topic throughout the week. The course will be held from 9am to 5pm each day.

This section of the course agenda outlines the schedule for the Vision Systems topic from January 6 to January 10, 2025. The main focus of this topic will be on developing an MVP (Minimum Viable Product) for vision systems, and there will be a workshop led by Si Scott and Allison Go. Additionally, there will be a written assessment test on January 10, 2025 at 15:58:02.
